<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Everyother person I pvp!</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?savej">savej</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:54 p.m. 19/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Everyother person I pvp!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2053" TARGET=_self>Re: Everyother person I pvp!</A> (Benign)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Ok I agree you like roleplaying PvP and such. Some don't, that's

<BR>&gt; their right, but lets not talk about that. I want to talk about
<BR>&gt; the instances you have been PKed. You said you were attacked 3
<BR>&gt; times by necros and you are a ranger. From on RP standpoint, why
<BR>&gt; would they talk to you about it? They have every reason in the
<BR>&gt; world to kill your fruity tree-huggin butt(don't take it
<BR>&gt; personal). The 2 you arent sure whats, if they werent your
<BR>&gt; race(or even if they were and knew ya), could still have RP
<BR>&gt; reasons to kill ya. They need not discuss this with you. They
<BR>&gt; attack when you are hurt? Well that's a shame, but you should be
<BR>&gt; more careful. You get upset about the situations that happened.
<BR>&gt; That is your fault not theirs. Let me tell you a little about my
<BR>&gt; experiences.
<P>&gt; I PK from time to time, usually invis and on people that are
<BR>&gt; fighting or hurt. I see no reason to give someone I am going to
<BR>&gt; kill a fair shot at killing me. They can sneak up and do the
<BR>&gt; same to me(if it is in character) or not(either is fine). I only
<BR>&gt; attack good races(even if they are grouped with bad races I
<BR>&gt; never initiate combat with bad races) and I rarely roleplay. I
<BR>&gt; figure if I don't say anything and they are role-players, they
<BR>&gt; can make up whatever reason they want. I will even go as far as
<BR>&gt; to play along with their story when they start giving me tells.
<BR>&gt; What "Children" is talking about is the people that
<BR>&gt; send countless tells about how I get beat up at home, am a
<BR>&gt; loser, going to get reported, etc. If your character is a
<BR>&gt; whiner, fine RP whine all you want. If you are really a
<BR>&gt; role-player like you say you are, you will come up with a reason
<BR>&gt; for each person that PKs you. When playing paper RPGs the GM
<BR>&gt; helps you with the story. In this game you have to do it all
<BR>&gt; yourelf or with other RPers. If you want to /OOC name call, you
<BR>&gt; are obviously on the wrong server. If you play on RZ you are
<BR>&gt; gonna die by other players for whatever reason they decide. This
<BR>&gt; you have to accept. No one group of players can "ruin"
<BR>&gt; the server because if the group of players is large enough to
<BR>&gt; "ruin" it then it will be run exactly how the majority
<BR>&gt; of players want it run. As for the 99% sure the RZ server wasn't
<BR>&gt; set up for... The RZ server was set up to make money, not for
<BR>&gt; any other purpose. If they could get 100,000 more customers on
<BR>&gt; RZ by adding a machine gun to the RZ server, I am sure they
<BR>&gt; would find the time.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
